1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Let's talk about managing spam on your website.

2
00:00:05,400 --> 00:00:08,400
Allowing comments on your website is a great way to connect with your readers or clients

3
00:00:09,360 --> 00:00:12,360
and build a community.

4
00:00:11,320 --> 00:00:14,320
Unfortunately allowing comments also opens the door for spammers.

5
00:00:15,560 --> 00:00:18,560
We have all received messages to become rich overnight or purchase unwanted products.

6
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:24,280
Comment spam happens when a spammer posts comments to your website via the blog or context page.

7
00:00:27,640 --> 00:00:30,640
In this lesson we will look at how you can manage and avoid spam on your website by using the

8
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:35,800
built-in features of WordPress and using an anti-spam plugin.

9
00:00:37,840 --> 00:00:40,840
Let's start with the built-in features.

10
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:43,360
By default WordPress comes with some built-in features to help you prevent spam on your

11
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:47,240
site which can be found in the settings discussion page in your dashboard.

12
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:55,040
Number 1.

13
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:56,040
Limiting the number of links allowed.

14
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:58,320
Since spam comments work through backlinks and encourage visitors to the spammer's site,

15
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:03,040
many spam comments will include a high number of links.

16
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:06,120
You may be able to catch some spam comments on your site by setting a limit to the number

17
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:10,680
of links allowed before it will be held for moderation or for an admin to approve.

18
00:01:13,160 --> 00:01:16,160
Just something to take note of.

19
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
The link limit is set to two links by default but you can lower it to one link per comment.

20
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:23,240
It is not recommended to set the limit to zero otherwise all comments will be held for

21
00:01:24,440 --> 00:01:27,440
moderation.

22
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:29,120
The second step you can take is to change the comment moderation settings.

23
00:01:30,520 --> 00:01:33,520
In addition to limiting the number of links in a comment, you can also apply specified

24
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:38,040
words, phrases, usernames, emails etc. in the comment moderation text field to automatically

25
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:44,560
hold comments containing these elements in the moderation queue.

26
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:49,400
As you will see I have selected words like gambling, insurance, win and a link to a cryptocurrency

27
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:54,440
website.

28
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:55,560
As these are things you will often see in spam comments but you are welcome to look at previous

29
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:59,640
comments to flag certain words.

30
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:02,880
Next you can also disallow comment keys or to put it differently you can have comments

31
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:08,600
with specified words or elements automatically deleted.

32
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:13,400
It is like the comment moderation setting but here you can specify words, phrases, usernames,

33
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:19,280
IP addresses and so forth to automatically place a comment in the trash.

34
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:24,800
This means you do not need to manually move the comment to the trash from the moderation

35
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:29,040
queue.

36
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:30,680
The fourth step you can take is to disable trackbacks.

37
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:34,520
A large part of spam is trackbacks.

38
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:37,000
Trackbacks and pingbacks notify you that another blog has linked to your content and

39
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:42,560
vice versa.

40
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:43,560
However, spammers often abuse this feature by sending trackbacks and pings from spam websites.

41
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:51,680
The last step you can take in the discussion page is to select all comments to be moderated.

42
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:57,840
You can do this by selecting Comment must be manually approved.

43
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Or you can of course choose not to receive any comments at all by deselecting Allow people

44
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:08,360
to submit comments.

45
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:12,160
Before we move on to plugins let's look at how to mark a comment as spam.

46
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:16,840
Go to comments and as you will see we have two spam comments here.

47
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:21,320
Click on both.

48
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:22,320
Cryptocurrency Mania and Win Big.

49
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:27,360
Go to the bulk action, mark as spam and then apply.

50
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:33,160
Next, another effective way to manage and stop spam is by using an anti-spam plugin.

51
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:40,720
There are many free and paid plugins that offer spam protection for your website which

52
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:45,560
you can find through the WordPress.org Plugin Directory.

53
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:49,520
Some plugins worth mentioning are Anti-spam Bee, Clean Talk or a Akismet.

54
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:57,760
There are multiple plugins to choose from in the Plugins Directory so find the one that

55
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:01,440
meets your needs.

56
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:03,560
In this example I am going to install and activate Akismet.

57
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:07,800
Make your way to plugins and click on Add new.

58
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:11,760
Select Akismet and then click on Install Now.

59
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:15,760
Wait a moment for installation to complete and then click on Activate.

60
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:20,640
Once you click activate you will be redirected to a page requesting that you set up an account

61
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:25,440
with Akismet.

62
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:26,840
Akismet is free for personal use so you can select what to pay even if it is $0.

63
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:32,360
So I will go ahead and drag the bar on the right to $0 and continue with a personal subscription.

64
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:38,840
And once activated there are a number of settings you can change for how you would like the

65
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:43,600
plugin to manage spam on your site.

66
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Let's look at a few more security plugins to consider.

67
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:51,080
CAPTCHA is a technology used to tell robots and humans apart.

68
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:55,600
Find the right CAPTCHA plugin as this makes it very hard for spam bots to infiltrate your

69
00:04:57,360 --> 00:05:00,360
website.

70
00:04:58,360 --> 00:05:01,360
Lastly, spam plugins can stop and delete a lot of spam comments but it can't stop spammers

71
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:07,120
from accessing your website.

72
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:09,240
Too many requests from spammers to submit comments can slow down your site and negatively affect

73
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:14,720
performance.

74
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:16,560
A firewall plugin such as All in one WordPress Security and Firewall, WordFence, Sucuri

75
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:23,040
or Jetpack will help you block unwanted requests before they even reach your site.

76
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:28,800
These plugins will ward off automated bots and scripts from trying to leave comments.

77
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,000
I trust these steps will help you secure your site and intercept spammers.

